1. create a project folder "PythonProjects" in d drive where your want
2. go to "PythonProjects" and open cmd (command prompt)

3. ğŸ‘‡ï¸ create virtual environment:  

        python -m venv venv

4. ğŸ‘‡ï¸ activate on Windows (cmd.exe):
      
        venv\Scripts\activate.bat

5. ğŸ‘‡ï¸ install django in the virtual environment:

        pip install django

6. ğŸ‘‡ï¸ create your django project:

      django-admin startproject Ecom
      
7. ğŸ‘‡ï¸ go to "Ecom":

      cd Ecom

8. ğŸ‘‡ï¸ run your project:

      python manage.py runserver
      
9. ğŸ‘‡ï¸ create project application(App_Login, App_Blog) inside project folder

	python  manage.py  startapp  App_Login
	python  manage.py  startapp  App_Shop
  python  manage.py  startapp  App_Order
  python  manage.py  startapp  App_Payment

10. ğŸ‘‡ï¸ install some package

	pip install Pillow   // for image upload
